description:
Use this function if you are asked to return the content of a file in a specific format (txt, html). Input: file path and optional desired format (default is 'txt'). Output: an object describing the result of the operation.

Return value:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "success" | "error",
"content": "string", // Converted file content
"error_message": "string | null" // Error details if status = 'error'
}

Example function call parameter: { "path": "/home/user/document.docx" }
Example function call parameter with format: { "path": "/home/user/document.docx", "format": "html" }

Example successful response:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "success",
"content": "File content in txt format...",
"error_message": null
}

Example error response:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "error",
"content": "",
"error_message": "Unsupported format requested."
}
